1
00:00:10,222 --> 00:00:12,986
Nao, with that girl... are you still talking?

2
00:00:13,244 --> 00:00:15,700
- Yeah.
- Why are you still talking to her?

3
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:17,546
She's kinda cute, you know.

4
00:00:18,231 --> 00:00:22,035
- Oh, Lin?
- You're Nao's friend, right? I'm Lin.

5
00:00:23,102 --> 00:00:26,346
I don't get you at all, Suer. Why are you always like this?

6
00:00:26,631 --> 00:00:30,102
- I want you in my life forever.
- That's not true, Nao.

7
00:00:30,564 --> 00:00:32,537
You've never been just my friend.

8
00:00:33,340 --> 00:00:34,497
I like you.

9
00:00:34,946 --> 00:00:38,577
- If it's not you, I don't want anyone else.
- Suer...

10
00:00:39,422 --> 00:00:40,546
Suer.

11
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:53,760
What's wrong, Duen?

12
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:57,288
Suer just came back into the room.

13
00:00:58,773 --> 00:01:00,724
He said he likes me.

14
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:03,413
Likes me... like in romance way.

15
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:05,671
Not just as a friend.

16
00:01:06,804 --> 00:01:08,564
Like a lover, Dan.

17
00:01:09,577 --> 00:01:11,635
I'm not joking, Dan.

18
00:01:11,933 --> 00:01:15,702
Now I understand why Suer doesn't want me to have anyone else.

19
00:01:16,128 --> 00:01:17,977
It's not because he's clingy.

20
00:01:18,420 --> 00:01:20,142
Or because he's jealous.

21
00:01:20,684 --> 00:01:25,226
He's liked me from the very beginning.
He never even saw me as a friend.

22
00:01:27,235 --> 00:01:29,053
Tiger told you he likes you?

23
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,457
You already knew, Dan?

24
00:01:33,284 --> 00:01:35,920
Yeah. I kind of noticed.

25
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,982
Since we used to be around him.

26
00:01:38,693 --> 00:01:42,786
You already knew? Why didn't you tell me?
This is serious.

27
00:01:43,213 --> 00:01:44,733
Why keep it a secret?

28
00:01:45,186 --> 00:01:48,840
I've always supported him having a girlfriend.

29
00:01:50,035 --> 00:01:53,222
Whoever I introduce him to, he never accepts.

30
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:56,146
And he always acts like he's already taken.

31
00:01:56,697 --> 00:02:01,013
At first, I thought he already had someone he liked.

32
00:02:03,768 --> 00:02:06,106
So it's me, huh.

33
00:02:07,324 --> 00:02:10,133
Are you disgusted that Tiger likes you?

34
00:02:12,351 --> 00:02:13,911
Who would be disgusted?

35
00:02:13,991 --> 00:02:15,666
Someone who has feelings for me?

36
00:02:16,093 --> 00:02:19,506
I'm just shocked that it's him.

37
00:02:21,008 --> 00:02:22,702
So what did you say to him?

38
00:02:23,644 --> 00:02:26,653
I didn't even get to answer.
He already walked away.

39
00:02:28,102 --> 00:02:29,662
I'll give you one week.

40
00:02:31,146 --> 00:02:32,346
Think about it.

41
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,613
Don't say yes just because you feel sorry.

42
00:02:38,031 --> 00:02:40,928
Or because you can't live without me.

43
00:02:43,853 --> 00:02:46,280
Otherwise, that would be really cruel to me.

44
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,982
Just think about it.

45
00:03:02,782 --> 00:03:06,315
Wow, that's pretty decisive.

46
00:03:06,777 --> 00:03:08,644
Tiger must be all in.

47
00:03:09,537 --> 00:03:11,573
Why does Suer like me?

48
00:03:11,995 --> 00:03:14,888
Since the beginning—six years already.

49
00:03:15,848 --> 00:03:17,902
Is it that hard to believe?

50
00:03:18,928 --> 00:03:21,577
I have always seen him as just a friend.

51
00:03:21,875 --> 00:03:23,751
But over those six years,

52
00:03:24,062 --> 00:03:26,613
why didn't I ever notice he liked me?

53
00:03:27,071 --> 00:03:28,400
Duen.

54
00:03:28,857 --> 00:03:30,968
Do you think you're not good enough?

55
00:03:31,417 --> 00:03:33,551
Stop thinking that and throw it away right now.

56
00:03:34,008 --> 00:03:35,586
Because the one who chose is Tiger.

57
00:03:35,915 --> 00:03:39,333
Tiger chose you, and he hasn't changed his mind for six years.

58
00:03:39,964 --> 00:03:42,031
Do you still think you're not good enough?

59
00:03:43,373 --> 00:03:45,804
What should I do? Dan, what should I do?

60
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,786
What do you think?

61
00:03:49,497 --> 00:03:50,893
I don't know.

62
00:03:52,497 --> 00:03:54,160
Why is it so hard?

63
00:03:54,302 --> 00:03:56,582
Then let me think about it.

64
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,408
Take your time.

65
00:03:58,551 --> 00:04:00,097
You still have seven days.

66
00:04:01,066 --> 00:04:04,057
Duen, I'm going to class now.

67
00:04:04,248 --> 00:04:07,093
I need to get to class. We'll talk later.

68
00:04:07,626 --> 00:04:10,395
- Bye-bye.
- Yeah, study hard, Dan.

69
00:05:51,364 --> 00:05:52,533
Singha.

70
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:54,653
I got news about P'Ben.

71
00:05:56,084 --> 00:05:58,035
Dad told him to send P'Ben to steal from two gangs.

72
00:06:00,826 --> 00:06:02,022
And who is he going with?

73
00:06:03,924 --> 00:06:04,880
Alone.

74
00:06:12,337 --> 00:06:14,164
Then he's definitely going to die happily.

75
00:06:15,328 --> 00:06:16,613
In a corpse state.

76
00:06:20,835 --> 00:06:22,457
Send me the details.

77
00:06:36,048 --> 00:06:36,911
It's me.

78
00:06:37,537 --> 00:06:39,342
Shit, where did you come from?

79
00:06:39,875 --> 00:06:41,044
You're safe now, Ben.

80
00:06:41,591 --> 00:06:42,871
I'll get you out of here.

81
00:06:45,648 --> 00:06:47,422
Take things to your father.

82
00:06:49,008 --> 00:06:52,368
After this, I'm quitting as your secretary.

83
00:06:54,426 --> 00:06:56,226
Why didn't you tell me?

84
00:06:57,448 --> 00:06:59,080
I just...

85
00:06:59,506 --> 00:07:01,004
I don't want to see your face anymore.

86
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:07,151
What? What did I do to you?

87
00:07:08,048 --> 00:07:09,933
What did I do wrong? Tell me.

88
00:07:10,226 --> 00:07:11,657
You didn't do anything wrong.

89
00:07:11,880 --> 00:07:13,408
I'm the one who's wrong.

90
00:07:14,204 --> 00:07:16,111
For loving an idiot like you.

91
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:18,355
You're about to get engaged.

92
00:07:19,226 --> 00:07:21,368
I just wanted to run away.

93
00:07:26,173 --> 00:07:27,380
Did you really mean that, Ben?

94
00:07:32,035 --> 00:07:34,684
If I survive this time,

95
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:37,000
and I can get away from you,

96
00:07:40,102 --> 00:07:42,128
I might forget you one day.

97
00:07:45,020 --> 00:07:46,577
I'll run away somewhere else.

98
00:07:47,364 --> 00:07:49,097
Find a girlfriend.

99
00:07:50,973 --> 00:07:54,226
Get married, have a family.

100
00:07:55,244 --> 00:07:57,924
And we probably won't meet again.

101
00:08:02,862 --> 00:08:05,448
I really love you, Singha.

102
00:08:08,693 --> 00:08:12,600
Ben, Ben, Ben, Ben.
What's wrong with you, Ben?

103
00:08:13,711 --> 00:08:14,733
Ben.

104
00:08:15,382 --> 00:08:17,204
Stay with me, Ben.

105
00:08:17,746 --> 00:08:18,768
Ben.

106
00:08:38,786 --> 00:08:40,471
Can you open your heart to me?

107
00:08:41,755 --> 00:08:43,253
Not as your best friend.

108
00:08:44,746 --> 00:08:46,333
But look at me...

109
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,293
as a man who loves you, Nao.

110
00:09:05,271 --> 00:09:06,111
North.

111
00:09:06,462 --> 00:09:07,684
I'm asking seriously.

112
00:09:08,217 --> 00:09:12,142
- You know about Suer, right?
- I don't know.

113
00:09:12,742 --> 00:09:15,306
- How would I know? Are you crazy?
- You know, you asshole.

114
00:09:15,377 --> 00:09:18,488
- I don't know.
- You know.
- How would I know?

115
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:21,568
North.

116
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:24,600
You're the loudmouth who tries to keep secrets, right?

117
00:09:27,155 --> 00:09:29,580
- No.
- You did well.

118
00:09:31,302 --> 00:09:36,000
But not enough, you bastard.
I know everything.

119
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:38,893
You guys really work well together, huh.

120
00:09:39,217 --> 00:09:41,844
You even kept me away from other people.

121
00:09:42,551 --> 00:09:44,520
Hah... what do you even know.

122
00:09:45,142 --> 00:09:47,533
I shouldn't have found out he likes you.

123
00:09:49,417 --> 00:09:50,937
So you knew all along?

124
00:09:53,253 --> 00:09:54,475
Yeah.

125
00:09:55,457 --> 00:09:56,380
And you?

126
00:09:56,906 --> 00:09:58,088
What are you going to do about him?

127
00:09:58,728 --> 00:10:00,300
You could've told me.

128
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:03,382
- I won't tell him.
- Damn it, I'm getting mad.

129
00:10:03,911 --> 00:10:05,253
So strict.

130
00:10:06,111 --> 00:10:08,435
North, let me ask you something.

131
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:12,400
Why didn't he say where he went?

132
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:14,471
Or did he forbid you from telling me?

133
00:10:14,617 --> 00:10:16,386
Hey, no!

134
00:10:16,706 --> 00:10:18,462
We don't know where he went either.

135
00:10:18,755 --> 00:10:20,608
We haven't seen him either.

136
00:10:21,253 --> 00:10:23,022
Hey, but he did call.

137
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,635
He asked about you.

138
00:10:25,053 --> 00:10:27,022
Just said, "How are you?" That's it.

139
00:10:29,564 --> 00:10:30,613
You guys...

140
00:10:31,031 --> 00:10:34,022
You guys... you, Mick, and Field?

141
00:10:34,422 --> 00:10:36,586
Yeah. That's everyone who knows.

142
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:42,342
So what are you going to do about Suer?

143
00:10:46,942 --> 00:10:48,462
I don't know.

144
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:52,182
North.

145
00:10:52,982 --> 00:10:54,257
Can you help me?

146
00:10:54,831 --> 00:10:56,377
Help me find him.

147
00:10:57,737 --> 00:10:58,502
Please.

148
00:11:10,097 --> 00:11:11,342
Why are you here again?

149
00:11:11,853 --> 00:11:12,888
How are you?

150
00:11:17,244 --> 00:11:18,648
Why don't you care about me?

151
00:11:19,382 --> 00:11:21,155
I told you I don't want to see your face.

152
00:11:22,711 --> 00:11:23,480
Why?

153
00:11:24,195 --> 00:11:25,453
Because you like me?

154
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,306
Yeah.

155
00:11:28,013 --> 00:11:29,648
Because it's impossible, Singha.

156
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,262
Now...

157
00:11:33,675 --> 00:11:35,524
I'm not your subordinate anymore.

158
00:11:36,297 --> 00:11:37,111
No.

159
00:11:37,746 --> 00:11:39,302
You're still mine.

160
00:11:40,706 --> 00:11:43,342
That diamond you stole...

161
00:11:43,924 --> 00:11:45,306
I'm not giving it to my father.

162
00:11:45,706 --> 00:11:47,715
You still have to stay with me, Ben.

163
00:11:50,977 --> 00:11:53,217
Don't you understand what I said?

164
00:11:56,142 --> 00:11:57,595
I said I like you.

165
00:11:57,940 --> 00:11:59,186
I love you.

166
00:12:00,142 --> 00:12:01,560
Not as a friend.

167
00:12:02,413 --> 00:12:04,444
And now you're getting married.

168
00:12:05,942 --> 00:12:08,533
You want me to just watch you be happy with someone else?

169
00:12:13,546 --> 00:12:15,346
Take the diamond to your father.

170
00:12:16,137 --> 00:12:18,368
- And then I can leave.
- No, Ben.

171
00:12:19,386 --> 00:12:21,160
I won't let you go anywhere, Ben.

172
00:12:22,813 --> 00:12:24,853
You're my best friend, you know that?

173
00:12:26,248 --> 00:12:27,340
Why?

174
00:12:29,777 --> 00:12:32,431
Through happiness and sadness...

175
00:12:33,315 --> 00:12:35,946
we've been through life and death so many times.

176
00:12:37,140 --> 00:12:38,822
Are you really going to leave me?

177
00:12:40,946 --> 00:12:42,893
You're holding me back with just the word "friend," huh?

178
00:12:44,035 --> 00:12:46,688
Did none of what I said get through to you?

179
00:12:47,453 --> 00:12:51,982
I like you as a lover, not as a friend.

180
00:12:53,146 --> 00:12:54,288
Do you understand?

181
00:12:58,026 --> 00:12:59,808
I'll always be with you.

182
00:13:00,457 --> 00:13:01,595
No matter what...

183
00:13:01,968 --> 00:13:03,235
or even death.

184
00:13:04,991 --> 00:13:08,431
I can't stand seeing you with someone else.

185
00:13:10,102 --> 00:13:12,528
I'm not with her, Ben.

186
00:13:13,048 --> 00:13:15,226
It's just a marriage in name only.

187
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,511
Either way, I'll still be with you.

188
00:13:18,711 --> 00:13:21,128
Why won't you just reject me, Singha?

189
00:13:22,066 --> 00:13:23,413
What do you really think of me?

190
00:13:23,737 --> 00:13:25,013
Tell me.

191
00:13:25,568 --> 00:13:27,413
Tell me honestly.

192
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,586
Go on.

193
00:13:36,871 --> 00:13:38,022
No, Ben.

194
00:13:41,182 --> 00:13:42,991
You're my best friend, Ben.

195
00:13:43,324 --> 00:13:44,911
I can't live without you.

196
00:13:46,266 --> 00:13:48,235
Just give me time to think.

197
00:13:48,826 --> 00:13:51,524
Don't leave yet. Give me time.

198
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:54,680
Go. I'm asking you.

199
00:13:58,951 --> 00:14:00,346
Let me go, Singha.

200
00:14:30,991 --> 00:14:32,537
When are you going home?

201
00:14:38,973 --> 00:14:40,497
Did father send you?

202
00:14:42,004 --> 00:14:43,151
Yeah.

203
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:49,560
You even refused to take a new secretary
and you just keep drinking.

204
00:14:53,844 --> 00:14:55,368
We found P’Ben.

205
00:14:55,862 --> 00:14:57,684
Who told you to look for Ben?

206
00:14:58,937 --> 00:15:01,560
I ordered that no one is allowed to look for him.

207
00:15:03,217 --> 00:15:04,180
Why?

208
00:15:12,706 --> 00:15:14,497
Because he wanted to leave.

209
00:15:16,697 --> 00:15:18,471
Huh?

210
00:15:22,395 --> 00:15:24,488
But if you keep working like this...

211
00:15:25,484 --> 00:15:27,186
Father will bring P’Ben back for sure.

212
00:15:34,786 --> 00:15:36,524
No one is allowed to look for Ben.

213
00:15:37,422 --> 00:15:38,706
I'll go back later.

214
00:15:42,395 --> 00:15:43,248
When?

215
00:15:45,911 --> 00:15:46,853
I don't know.

216
00:15:52,235 --> 00:15:53,777
I'll handle things for now.

217
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:55,920
But don't take too long.

218
00:15:56,817 --> 00:15:58,697
Because I'm already messed up enough as it is.

219
00:16:26,493 --> 00:16:28,540
Don't bother me.

220
00:16:35,191 --> 00:16:36,760
I said don't bother me.

221
00:16:37,644 --> 00:16:40,075
Suer, you're really here.

222
00:16:42,995 --> 00:16:44,013
Suer.

223
00:16:44,577 --> 00:16:46,128
Open the door for me.

224
00:16:47,195 --> 00:16:48,386
It's me.

225
00:16:49,044 --> 00:16:49,960
Nao.

226
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:53,293
Are you really going to make me stand here talking to myself?

227
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:55,915
Open the door.

228
00:16:56,262 --> 00:16:58,702
Aren't you afraid of disturbing the neighbors?

229
00:17:02,115 --> 00:17:04,644
Suer, I'm getting mad.

230
00:17:07,942 --> 00:17:08,924
Suer.

231
00:17:13,386 --> 00:17:15,160
Ouch, hey—

232
00:17:15,293 --> 00:17:17,831
- Don’t hurt me.
- Nao.

233
00:17:17,888 --> 00:17:19,355
- Hey, Nao.
- I just came to visit a friend.

234
00:17:21,048 --> 00:17:22,982
Do you want me to act like I got attacked first?

235
00:17:27,302 --> 00:17:29,017
Suer.

236
00:17:29,164 --> 00:17:34,382
- Open it first.
- What?
- Talk to me first.

237
00:17:34,528 --> 00:17:36,662
- Ow.
- Hey.

238
00:17:36,982 --> 00:17:39,088
Are you okay?

239
00:17:42,648 --> 00:17:45,568
Alright… let’s give this a try.

240
00:18:04,435 --> 00:18:05,684
Confused, huh?

241
00:18:07,008 --> 00:18:08,506
When you told me...

242
00:18:08,795 --> 00:18:09,946
I was confused too.

243
00:18:14,297 --> 00:18:16,373
Why do you like me, Suer?

244
00:18:23,075 --> 00:18:24,342
Because you're cute.

245
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,951
You're really cute, Nao.

246
00:18:32,555 --> 00:18:33,782
At first...

247
00:18:35,115 --> 00:18:36,666
I hated my family a lot.

248
00:18:38,546 --> 00:18:41,453
Work,

249
00:18:42,177 --> 00:18:44,662
my parents,

250
00:18:45,328 --> 00:18:46,591
and even my brother.

251
00:18:50,177 --> 00:18:51,700
But when I met you...

252
00:18:53,660 --> 00:18:54,946
and stayed at your house...

253
00:18:55,620 --> 00:18:56,822
I...

254
00:19:03,657 --> 00:19:05,377
I finally had a real home.

255
00:19:07,826 --> 00:19:09,453
A home full of smiles...

256
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:11,226
and laughter.

257
00:19:14,657 --> 00:19:16,257
No stress...

258
00:19:16,706 --> 00:19:17,973
no pressure.

259
00:19:19,915 --> 00:19:21,100
yeah.

260
00:19:23,377 --> 00:19:26,200
Everyone took care of me...

261
00:19:27,026 --> 00:19:28,684
and treated me so well.

262
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:33,680
I really love that house.

263
00:19:36,622 --> 00:19:37,595
And you...

264
00:19:41,728 --> 00:19:44,075
you never suspected anything about me.

265
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:48,440
Even when I came back covered in blood...

266
00:19:50,066 --> 00:19:51,648
you only asked...

267
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:53,173
if I was okay...

268
00:19:54,275 --> 00:19:55,568
if I was hurt anywhere.

269
00:19:58,977 --> 00:20:00,648
You always gave me advice...

270
00:20:02,471 --> 00:20:04,875
helped me see things differently.

271
00:20:06,573 --> 00:20:08,560
until I finally opened up to Singha.

272
00:20:10,613 --> 00:20:12,546
and things between us got better.

273
00:20:17,146 --> 00:20:18,897
Without you...

274
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:23,142
I don’t know

275
00:20:23,493 --> 00:20:25,040
what I’d be like now.

276
00:20:26,835 --> 00:20:28,675
You’re someone I have fun with...

277
00:20:29,857 --> 00:20:31,044
someone who makes me happy.

278
00:20:32,382 --> 00:20:34,164
I really like being with you.

279
00:20:35,373 --> 00:20:36,346
until...

280
00:20:40,084 --> 00:20:42,320
I realized I couldn’t live without you.

281
00:20:44,946 --> 00:20:46,613
So I don’t want to let you go to anyone else.

282
00:20:52,164 --> 00:20:53,511
What you just said...

283
00:20:54,342 --> 00:20:55,524
is it true?

284
00:20:57,728 --> 00:20:59,062
About giving it a try?

285
00:21:00,075 --> 00:21:01,137
Yes.

286
00:21:02,146 --> 00:21:03,302
Let’s try it.

287
00:21:07,537 --> 00:21:08,311
So...

288
00:21:09,444 --> 00:21:10,537
we’re dating now?

289
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:14,924
No.

290
00:21:15,622 --> 00:21:16,684
I mean...

291
00:21:17,577 --> 00:21:18,702
just trying.

292
00:21:19,671 --> 00:21:21,582
Trying to open my heart to you.

293
00:21:22,155 --> 00:21:23,533
That’s already opening up.

294
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:25,551
Isn’t that basically dating?

295
00:21:26,488 --> 00:21:27,568
Or is it...

296
00:21:28,173 --> 00:21:29,511
what kind of opening up is it?

297
00:21:30,431 --> 00:21:32,706
It means I’m letting you try to court me.

298
00:21:43,106 --> 00:21:46,360
Suer... why are you crying?

299
00:21:49,724 --> 00:21:51,608
Did I do something wrong?

300
00:21:53,031 --> 00:21:54,542
You didn’t do anything wrong.

301
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:56,737
I’m just happy.

302
00:22:00,751 --> 00:22:02,728
I thought you were going to reject me.

303
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:05,431
I was so scared.

304
00:22:06,866 --> 00:22:08,831
Scared that we wouldn’t be together anymore.

305
00:22:12,004 --> 00:22:13,568
Stop crying.

306
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,840
I didn’t reject you.

307
00:22:18,937 --> 00:22:20,560
Even if I haven’t agreed to be your boyfriend,

308
00:22:21,128 --> 00:22:23,040
I’m giving you a chance to try and pursue me.

309
00:22:28,137 --> 00:22:30,604
I’m really happy.

310
00:22:32,115 --> 00:22:33,648
Thank you, Nao.

311
00:22:40,377 --> 00:22:43,440
Such a crybaby, Suer.

312
00:23:08,715 --> 00:23:10,862
your tiger: I’ve arrived at class.

313
00:23:21,204 --> 00:23:25,248
your tiger: I didn’t secretly sit with anyone, just friends.

314
00:23:31,173 --> 00:23:32,724
your tiger: Have you reached class yet?

315
00:23:33,048 --> 00:23:35,008
your tiger: Study hard, don’t fail the exam again.

316
00:23:35,462 --> 00:23:38,315
your tiger: Don’t sit with anyone else—if there’s no seat,

317
00:23:38,622 --> 00:23:40,995
your tiger: just sit at the teacher’s desk. Love you.

318
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:48,604
your tiger: I love Nao the most in the worldddd
and I miss you toooo.

319
00:23:48,902 --> 00:23:53,217
your tiger: Be careful on the stairs.
I’ll reserve a table for you at the cafeteria.

320
00:23:53,591 --> 00:23:55,493
your tiger: Call me after class.

321
00:23:55,866 --> 00:23:58,573
your tiger: Want anything? I’ll buy it for you first.

322
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:02,986
your tiger: Hey, why aren’t you replying?

323
00:24:04,364 --> 00:24:06,515
your tiger: But I still love you the most.

324
00:24:17,746 --> 00:24:22,600
I think he’s getting repressed.
Spamming you like this—just reply to him.

325
00:24:22,968 --> 00:24:25,124
The more I reply, the more he sends.

326
00:24:25,324 --> 00:24:29,217
Are you annoyed with him?

327
00:24:32,302 --> 00:24:34,577
He’s Suer. How could I be annoyed?

328
00:24:35,768 --> 00:24:39,097
Even if he came to sit and watch me in class, I’d be fine.

329
00:24:40,195 --> 00:24:41,653
You’re going too far.

330
00:24:42,222 --> 00:24:45,586
If it’s that much, why don’t you two just date already?

331
00:24:47,422 --> 00:24:49,142
Suer is important to me,

332
00:24:49,986 --> 00:24:52,600
but I want to take things slow when it comes to dating.

333
00:24:54,213 --> 00:24:55,946
“Take things slow”?

334
00:24:56,715 --> 00:24:58,822
- I’ll slap you.
- I’ll poke you.

335
00:24:59,980 --> 00:25:01,742
I’ll hit you back—watch yourself.

336
00:25:11,871 --> 00:25:13,528
Oh, Suer.

337
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:15,342
What are you doing here?

338
00:25:16,022 --> 00:25:18,466
Get, sorry about that.

339
00:25:18,808 --> 00:25:20,244
Can I sit here?

340
00:25:21,102 --> 00:25:22,444
Why should I let you sit here?

341
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:28,911
Hey.

342
00:25:29,871 --> 00:25:30,968
What do you say?

343
00:25:34,342 --> 00:25:35,715
Yes, boss.

344
00:25:36,204 --> 00:25:39,066
Sure, go ahead.
Sit, sit.

345
00:25:39,395 --> 00:25:40,608
I’ll sit behind you.

346
00:25:42,017 --> 00:25:43,271
Don’t you have class?

347
00:25:44,364 --> 00:25:45,484
Skip class of course.

348
00:25:46,248 --> 00:25:47,328
For what?

349
00:25:49,022 --> 00:25:50,644
Because I miss you.

350
00:25:50,937 --> 00:25:52,600
You weren’t replying to my texts.

351
00:25:54,444 --> 00:25:56,031
How am I supposed to reply?

352
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:57,773
I’m in class.

353
00:25:58,453 --> 00:26:00,342
You were the one who told me to study hard.

354
00:26:01,120 --> 00:26:04,035
Can’t you text and study at the same time?

355
00:26:05,044 --> 00:26:06,924
I can’t split my focus.

356
00:26:07,053 --> 00:26:09,253
And you? Why aren’t you studying?

357
00:26:12,568 --> 00:26:13,964
You go study.

358
00:26:14,142 --> 00:26:15,124
I won’t bother you anymore.

359
00:26:27,804 --> 00:26:29,106
I told you already.

360
00:26:30,417 --> 00:26:32,391
He’s crazy about you.

361
00:26:34,213 --> 00:26:35,528
Nonsense, idiot.

362
00:26:35,697 --> 00:26:38,391
Nonsense? Open your eyes and look.

363
00:26:39,368 --> 00:26:42,177
Just wait and see.

364
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:43,820
You’ll see.

365
00:26:44,204 --> 00:26:45,168
What is it?

366
00:26:47,511 --> 00:26:48,960
Damn, nonsense.

367
00:26:49,506 --> 00:26:50,613
Calling me nonsense again.

368
00:27:08,364 --> 00:27:09,768
What’s wrong with you, North?

369
00:27:11,555 --> 00:27:12,520
Nothing.

370
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:16,048
Nothing? Tell me.

371
00:27:16,586 --> 00:27:17,977
Nothing at all.

372
00:27:18,822 --> 00:27:19,662
North.

373
00:27:20,862 --> 00:27:24,551
At first I didn’t suspect anything… but now I do.

374
00:27:26,466 --> 00:27:27,760
What.

375
00:27:28,195 --> 00:27:29,573
Is it about Suer?

376
00:27:32,706 --> 00:27:33,546
Yeah.

377
00:27:34,306 --> 00:27:36,493
You probably already figured it out.

378
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:39,124
He’s totally crazy about you.

379
00:27:41,835 --> 00:27:43,822
He’s planning a surprise for you.

380
00:27:43,964 --> 00:27:45,342
That’s all I can say.

381
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:48,500
What surprise?

382
00:27:56,380 --> 00:27:58,235
What kind of guy do you want to be pursued by?

383
00:28:00,866 --> 00:28:02,711
Do people even ask that?

384
00:28:04,324 --> 00:28:06,800
So you like surprises, huh.

385
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:10,106
How about a campus-wide vinyl banner?

386
00:28:18,871 --> 00:28:20,142
So that’s a yes.

387
00:28:23,140 --> 00:28:24,231
Hey, you’re blushing?

388
00:28:26,693 --> 00:28:28,008
I don’t know.

389
00:28:43,186 --> 00:28:44,617
A vinyl banner.

390
00:28:53,977 --> 00:28:55,924
I love you, Duennao.

391
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:59,742
Shit… a vinyl banner.

392
00:29:00,026 --> 00:29:02,342
Hey, Nao, where are you going?

393
00:29:02,342 --> 00:29:05,340
Hey, stop—stop!

394
00:29:06,173 --> 00:29:08,480
Hey!

395
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:12,435
Um… is this Suer’s banner?

396
00:29:12,733 --> 00:29:14,280
Can you take it down first?

397
00:29:14,537 --> 00:29:15,804
Who are you?

398
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:17,915
How dare you call Khun Tiger “that guy”?

399
00:29:18,484 --> 00:29:21,017
Uh… I’m Duennao.

400
00:29:21,133 --> 00:29:22,982
My name should be on that banner, right?

401
00:29:25,608 --> 00:29:27,170
Oops, ma’am.

402
00:29:27,346 --> 00:29:28,235
I'm sorry.

403
00:29:28,902 --> 00:29:32,240
We weren’t careful and used inappropriate words and behavior.

404
00:29:32,671 --> 00:29:34,137
Please forgive us.

405
00:29:36,340 --> 00:29:37,208
Uh…

406
00:29:37,591 --> 00:29:38,684
Ma’am?

407
00:29:40,484 --> 00:29:41,693
Let’s leave that for now, sir.

408
00:29:41,946 --> 00:29:43,808
Can you just take it up first?

409
00:29:44,888 --> 00:29:49,351
- But Khun Tiger…
- I’ll talk to Suer myself, sir.

410
00:29:49,906 --> 00:29:53,564
- Or you can just throw it away first.
- Would that be okay?

411
00:29:54,071 --> 00:29:56,160
He put a lot of effort into it, you know.

412
00:29:56,693 --> 00:29:59,804
Then you can just keep it for now, sir.

413
00:29:59,942 --> 00:30:01,493
Understood, ma’am.

414
00:30:02,484 --> 00:30:03,533
Hey, take it down.

415
00:30:09,231 --> 00:30:11,208
- Gosh
- You really made them take it down?

416
00:30:11,933 --> 00:30:13,137
Yeah.

417
00:30:14,164 --> 00:30:17,435
What the hell is that over-the-top nonsense?
I should’ve punched him once.

418
00:30:17,591 --> 00:30:19,528
Hey, come on.

419
00:30:19,826 --> 00:30:21,688
He probably thought you’d like it.

420
00:30:21,986 --> 00:30:25,080
That’s just how Tiger is, like a clueless kid.

421
00:30:25,893 --> 00:30:29,973
But he did it because he really wanted to impress the person he likes.

422
00:30:30,604 --> 00:30:32,226
Don’t be mad at him.

423
00:30:33,408 --> 00:30:34,951
Listen.

424
00:30:35,951 --> 00:30:37,884
I did warn him at first.

425
00:30:38,053 --> 00:30:39,951
But when I saw how happy he was…

426
00:30:40,284 --> 00:30:42,031
I just couldn’t say anything.

427
00:30:46,213 --> 00:30:48,111
But I’m definitely not impressed.

428
00:30:48,742 --> 00:30:50,880
Look how huge that sign is.

429
00:30:51,506 --> 00:30:52,404
True.

430
00:30:52,780 --> 00:30:54,484
Probably scared people wouldn’t see it.

431
00:30:54,740 --> 00:30:57,942
Hey North, did you tell that Suer went to ask P’Jo?

432
00:30:58,315 --> 00:31:01,186
- Did P’Jo mess with him?
- No, he didn’t.

433
00:31:02,497 --> 00:31:05,777
He just asked how he should woo me.

434
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:08,133
What did P’Jo say?

435
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,582
“Go all out.”

436
00:31:10,928 --> 00:31:12,426
Oh my god.

437
00:31:13,426 --> 00:31:14,591
Unbelievable.

438
00:31:14,910 --> 00:31:18,000
See? I told you. See how big it is?

439
00:31:18,591 --> 00:31:19,182
Hey.

440
00:31:19,266 --> 00:31:20,933
Hey, Nao!

441
00:31:22,662 --> 00:31:23,853
Suer.

442
00:31:24,644 --> 00:31:26,453
Don’t look at North like that.

443
00:31:37,860 --> 00:31:40,346
So you really don’t like surprises that much?

444
00:31:44,008 --> 00:31:45,493
It’s not that I don’t like them.

445
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:49,191
It’s just… I don’t think it suits me.

446
00:31:53,217 --> 00:31:54,715
Yeah.

447
00:31:55,386 --> 00:31:58,422
It’s nice that you did it for me.

448
00:31:59,177 --> 00:31:59,968
But…

449
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:02,448
I’m just a simple person.

450
00:32:08,510 --> 00:32:09,920
That means it’s just…

451
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:12,457
no different from anyone else.

452
00:32:14,502 --> 00:32:16,551
If someone comes to woo you…

453
00:32:17,875 --> 00:32:19,404
then it won’t be different either.

454
00:32:21,648 --> 00:32:24,900
- If someone comes to woo me, you’d let them?
- No way.

455
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:28,964
Exactly.

456
00:32:29,506 --> 00:32:31,200
Then why compete with them…

457
00:32:31,786 --> 00:32:34,568
when right now I’m the only one trying to woo you?

458
00:32:34,928 --> 00:32:37,351
No one else is allowed to try.

459
00:32:41,008 --> 00:32:42,386
So sweet.

460
00:32:43,271 --> 00:32:45,017
Hey, what am I even doing here?

461
00:32:47,035 --> 00:32:49,200
North, shut up. You’re narrating again.

462
00:32:50,186 --> 00:32:52,226
Hey, it’s not my fault!

463
00:32:52,675 --> 00:32:54,484
I came all the way here just to keep you company.

464
00:33:02,453 --> 00:33:03,320
Hey.

465
00:33:05,177 --> 00:33:05,991
Hey.

466
00:33:06,386 --> 00:33:07,071
Hmm?

467
00:33:08,204 --> 00:33:09,155
Tomorrow…

468
00:33:09,782 --> 00:33:10,995
let’s go watch a movie.

469
00:33:12,546 --> 00:33:13,671
Okay, sure.

470
00:33:25,093 --> 00:33:26,582
What movie should we watch?

471
00:33:28,293 --> 00:33:29,271
Let’s go.

472
00:33:29,724 --> 00:33:31,706
Go where? We haven’t even bought tickets yet.

473
00:33:32,177 --> 00:33:34,840
- No need to buy them. Come on.
- Why?

474
00:33:35,231 --> 00:33:37,248
So what are we actually watching?

475
00:33:38,542 --> 00:33:40,906
A special one.

476
00:33:41,340 --> 00:33:43,062
A surprise.

477
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:44,404
Special?

478
00:33:47,897 --> 00:33:49,684
Seriously, what is it?

479
00:33:51,288 --> 00:33:52,404
What movie is it?

480
00:33:53,164 --> 00:33:54,173
We’re almost there.

481
00:33:54,591 --> 00:33:55,924
Huh?

482
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:00,471
Wait…

483
00:34:01,128 --> 00:34:02,155
Why…

484
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:04,315
we're on the poster?

485
00:34:04,782 --> 00:34:05,760
Well…

486
00:34:05,977 --> 00:34:07,711
I bought the rights to this film.

487
00:34:08,542 --> 00:34:11,177
You kept saying that the original male lead was…

488
00:34:11,493 --> 00:34:12,368
cool.

489
00:34:13,044 --> 00:34:14,511
so…

490
00:34:14,751 --> 00:34:17,431
I replaced the lead with my face.

491
00:34:18,173 --> 00:34:19,186
Suer!

492
00:34:19,826 --> 00:34:21,137
What are you doing?!

493
00:34:21,924 --> 00:34:23,213
Come on.

494
00:34:23,608 --> 00:34:26,097
Seriously?

495
00:34:27,404 --> 00:34:28,888
I’m asking seriously.

496
00:34:29,871 --> 00:34:31,813
What are you laughing at, idiot?!

497
00:34:33,097 --> 00:34:35,053
I can’t even be mad at him.

498
00:34:35,808 --> 00:34:37,848
I was going to scold him, but I can’t.

499
00:34:39,804 --> 00:34:41,702
Don’t just look at the result…

500
00:34:42,431 --> 00:34:45,524
look at his effort and how much he tried.

501
00:34:46,031 --> 00:34:47,848
Hey, North, you bastard.

502
00:34:48,008 --> 00:34:49,840
You’re really on his side, huh?

503
00:34:53,773 --> 00:34:55,071
Hey, North.

504
00:34:55,780 --> 00:34:57,404
But I’m worried he might have another plan.

505
00:34:57,702 --> 00:35:00,004
- What should we do?
- Just accept it.

506
00:35:00,608 --> 00:35:01,764
Accept what?

507
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:04,262
There’s nothing we can do anyway.

508
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:06,186
Or are you gonna give him up?

509
00:35:08,662 --> 00:35:11,386
Yeah… see? You still like him.

510
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:14,871
Yeah… it does feel good.

511
00:35:16,235 --> 00:35:19,471
- If he keeps going this over the top…
- You’ll stop liking him?

512
00:35:19,640 --> 00:35:21,546
This is giving me a headache, damn it.

513
00:35:25,635 --> 00:35:26,684
He’s really bold, huh.

514
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:30,871
Cheers.

515
00:35:34,737 --> 00:35:36,533
Why did you call us here so suddenly?

516
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:38,373
It’s Mick.

517
00:35:38,946 --> 00:35:41,297
Uh… where is he?

518
00:35:43,031 --> 00:35:44,408
He’s still not here.

519
00:35:44,875 --> 00:35:47,924
His chat isn’t replying, and he’s not picking up.

520
00:35:48,422 --> 00:35:50,835
- He was the one who called us, though.
- Yeah.

521
00:35:51,146 --> 00:35:55,133
- What is going on with him?
- Does anyone know why he’s so down?

522
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,831
No idea.

523
00:35:59,262 --> 00:36:00,057
No clue.

524
00:36:00,386 --> 00:36:03,057
Hey, what about Ger? He’s not coming?

525
00:36:04,302 --> 00:36:05,706
He said he had something urgent.

526
00:36:10,684 --> 00:36:12,022
Hey!

527
00:36:13,417 --> 00:36:15,297
Mick, what’s wrong with you?

528
00:36:18,100 --> 00:36:19,542
Hey, hey!

529
00:36:21,222 --> 00:36:21,871
He’s done.

530
00:36:22,906 --> 00:36:24,293
Mick, what’s going on?

531
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:30,364
Hey, that's not your glass.

532
00:36:30,795 --> 00:36:33,146
I’m going to pour for you, calm down.

533
00:36:33,653 --> 00:36:34,502
Jeez.

534
00:36:38,302 --> 00:36:39,080
You guys really don’t know?

535
00:36:39,182 --> 00:36:41,413
What’s wrong with him?

536
00:36:43,671 --> 00:36:44,782
Hey, that’s mine!

537
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:47,235
He’s drinking everything—just give him the bottle.

538
00:36:47,420 --> 00:36:49,226
Yeah, give him the bottle.

539
00:36:49,795 --> 00:36:51,164
Shit.

540
00:36:51,688 --> 00:36:52,800
Mick!

541
00:36:53,933 --> 00:36:56,973
If you don’t talk, we can’t help you.

542
00:36:57,737 --> 00:37:01,506
Yeah, just tell us. We can help you.

543
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:03,488
Hey…

544
00:37:03,835 --> 00:37:05,546
Maybe he’s not ready yet.

545
00:37:05,995 --> 00:37:09,017
Let him drink. Pour him more.

546
00:37:11,168 --> 00:37:14,720
He’s already had four glasses.

547
00:37:17,222 --> 00:37:18,471
Let him drink first.

548
00:37:18,693 --> 00:37:20,471
- People talk when they’re drunk.
- True.

549
00:37:20,791 --> 00:37:25,213
Come on, cheers! Drink!

550
00:37:33,191 --> 00:37:35,862
It’s about… Tul…

551
00:37:36,346 --> 00:37:38,053
Tul…

552
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,355
Hey!

553
00:38:35,084 --> 00:38:37,737
Ugh… I just wanna sleep.

554
00:38:39,066 --> 00:38:42,311
He said he’s liked me for a long time.

555
00:38:43,208 --> 00:38:44,933
But I only saw him as a friend.

556
00:38:45,773 --> 00:38:48,008
And now… we’re not even friends anymore.

557
00:38:55,804 --> 00:38:58,435
I wanted to take responsibility for it…

558
00:38:58,622 --> 00:39:00,204
But he wouldn’t accept it.

559
00:39:00,453 --> 00:39:03,391
He told me to forget him.

560
00:39:03,782 --> 00:39:05,871
Because he thinks I could never love him.

561
00:39:07,337 --> 00:39:08,982
Calm down, okay?

562
00:39:09,742 --> 00:39:12,395
He thinks that because he already decided.

563
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:17,608
Back when you liked someone, you always asked him for advice.

564
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:19,737
So he probably thought you didn’t like him.

565
00:39:20,111 --> 00:39:22,675
And that you never would.

566
00:39:24,133 --> 00:39:27,751
Give me a chance… let me try.

567
00:39:28,844 --> 00:39:32,022
Why do you get to decide I can’t love him?

568
00:39:33,164 --> 00:39:34,688
But what if Tul is right?

569
00:39:34,853 --> 00:39:36,800
What if you’re just pitying him?

570
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:38,448
Not actually loving him?

571
00:39:38,742 --> 00:39:41,484
Then the one who gets hurt is him, right?

572
00:39:42,008 --> 00:39:44,764
- Makes sense, bro. Come on.
- Let’s drink.

573
00:39:48,488 --> 00:39:49,551
Mick…

574
00:39:51,231 --> 00:39:53,453
So you… can you love him?

575
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,928
I don’t know.

576
00:40:03,035 --> 00:40:05,817
I really like him as a friend.

577
00:40:06,911 --> 00:40:08,937
He’s my closest friend.

578
00:40:10,831 --> 00:40:13,666
I don’t want to lose him.

579
00:40:14,733 --> 00:40:16,080
What should I do?

580
00:40:16,715 --> 00:40:19,160
I think…

581
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:20,995
we should call him and clear things up.

582
00:40:22,586 --> 00:40:24,017
Yeah, North, call him.

583
00:40:24,457 --> 00:40:26,315
Why me?

584
00:40:26,662 --> 00:40:28,448
You’re the closest to him.

585
00:40:29,515 --> 00:40:30,404
Just call him.

586
00:40:30,551 --> 00:40:33,626
- Just call him.
- Hey, you’re so slow, Nao.

587
00:40:33,804 --> 00:40:37,662
- Huh? Need me to teach you a lesson?
- You’ll get punched like last time.

588
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:39,946
I’ll elbow you, asshole.

589
00:40:40,142 --> 00:40:43,862
Do you see how upset he is? Hurry up.

590
00:40:44,168 --> 00:40:46,453
- I’m calling now.
- Go on.

591
00:40:47,288 --> 00:40:48,315
Okay.

592
00:40:52,097 --> 00:40:53,355
Hello?

593
00:40:55,186 --> 00:40:56,231
Tul?

594
00:40:56,462 --> 00:40:58,866
- Wanna hang out?
- Hang out?

595
00:40:59,302 --> 00:41:01,577
You’re gonna make me talk to Mick, right?

596
00:41:02,564 --> 00:41:03,924
Shit…

597
00:41:04,220 --> 00:41:07,440
How did you know? He’s been crying like crazy.

598
00:41:10,951 --> 00:41:12,960
Don’t you feel bad for him?

599
00:41:13,302 --> 00:41:15,351
I don’t care anymore. It’s over.

600
00:41:15,862 --> 00:41:17,066
Tul…

601
00:41:17,168 --> 00:41:18,848
You’re so cruel

602
00:41:19,844 --> 00:41:21,311
I know you

603
00:41:22,044 --> 00:41:23,897
can’t let go of him

604
00:41:24,804 --> 00:41:26,635
Why don’t you give him a chance?

605
00:41:28,920 --> 00:41:30,400
So you’re trying to convince me

606
00:41:32,004 --> 00:41:33,720
Yeah, come on, Tul

607
00:41:34,217 --> 00:41:36,173
Just give him a chance

608
00:41:36,560 --> 00:41:38,155
In the end, if you get hurt

609
00:41:38,497 --> 00:41:40,466
at least you’ve tried

610
00:41:43,420 --> 00:41:45,026
Alright, I’ll go

611
00:41:46,013 --> 00:41:48,130
See you, man

612
00:41:49,195 --> 00:41:53,826
Hey, he is  coming—cheers!

613
00:41:53,946 --> 00:41:55,413
Good job, Nao

614
00:41:56,008 --> 00:42:00,600
You really saved me
Cheers, bottoms up

615
00:42:03,337 --> 00:42:05,608
So Tul finally opened up to Mick, right?

616
00:42:06,831 --> 00:42:08,964
Yeah, thanks to me.

617
00:42:10,404 --> 00:42:14,057
Nice. And the advisor, how are you?

618
00:42:16,146 --> 00:42:18,831
Let Tiger come and court you—how’s it going?

619
00:42:19,964 --> 00:42:21,111
Hmm

620
00:42:22,511 --> 00:42:23,648
I don’t know

621
00:42:23,942 --> 00:42:28,500
It feels strange. He doesn’t usually do this

622
00:42:29,537 --> 00:42:30,733
Do you like it?

623
00:42:31,071 --> 00:42:32,933
What are you asking, Dan?

624
00:42:34,173 --> 00:42:35,537
I get it now

625
00:42:36,435 --> 00:42:38,880
Get what? I haven’t even said anything

626
00:42:49,746 --> 00:42:51,880
Hey

627
00:42:55,186 --> 00:42:56,875
Okay

628
00:43:01,820 --> 00:43:03,275
Why are you riding so recklessly?

629
00:43:03,568 --> 00:43:08,142
Pay for the damage. I’m in a hurry
Young people these days don’t look where they’re going

630
00:43:08,533 --> 00:43:11,288
You cut me off. Check the CCTV

631
00:43:11,515 --> 00:43:12,488
There is one nearby

632
00:43:12,804 --> 00:43:15,408
Watch your tone. Do you know who I am?

633
00:43:15,617 --> 00:43:17,902
If I take this further, you won’t get away with it

634
00:43:18,666 --> 00:43:20,217
Go ahead, call them

635
00:43:20,551 --> 00:43:21,742
I’m not scared

636
00:43:24,297 --> 00:43:26,017
You think you’re the only one who can make calls?

637
00:43:33,991 --> 00:43:35,404
Hey

638
00:43:36,560 --> 00:43:37,568
Yeah?

639
00:43:38,391 --> 00:43:39,857
Suer, what are you doing?

640
00:43:41,631 --> 00:43:42,680
Are you in class?

641
00:43:45,102 --> 00:43:46,800
Yeah

642
00:43:48,386 --> 00:43:50,422
Something came up

643
00:43:53,257 --> 00:43:54,364
Come see me

644
00:44:07,302 --> 00:44:08,804
Are you okay?

645
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:10,373
Uh…

646
00:44:10,755 --> 00:44:13,373
Just some scratches on my elbow and knee

647
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:22,275
Hey, what are you doing?

648
00:44:22,453 --> 00:44:24,008
Your pants are torn

649
00:44:24,351 --> 00:44:26,100
Everyone can see your legs

650
00:44:27,826 --> 00:44:29,920
It’s not that revealing

651
00:44:32,422 --> 00:44:34,293
I’m not embarrassed people can see my legs

652
00:44:34,706 --> 00:44:36,511
I’m just embarrassed it’s torn

653
00:44:37,231 --> 00:44:39,248
But thanks

654
00:44:40,031 --> 00:44:43,328
So what now? Are you going to pay for the damage?

655
00:44:46,822 --> 00:44:48,195
Wait

656
00:44:48,600 --> 00:44:49,875
Wait in the car first

657
00:44:50,337 --> 00:44:51,408
I’ll handle it

658
00:44:52,391 --> 00:44:53,817
But it’s my bike

659
00:44:54,657 --> 00:44:56,610
Wouldn’t it be better if I don’t go?

660
00:44:59,862 --> 00:45:01,120
It’s fine

661
00:45:27,511 --> 00:45:28,511
How is it?

662
00:45:32,333 --> 00:45:33,200
Let me see

663
00:45:36,368 --> 00:45:37,328
Just a little

664
00:45:43,151 --> 00:45:45,391
I’ve already handled it. Don’t worry

665
00:45:46,084 --> 00:45:47,724
The bike is being repaired

666
00:45:49,013 --> 00:45:50,688
Meanwhile

667
00:45:51,071 --> 00:45:52,946
I’ll get you a new one to use

668
00:45:54,626 --> 00:45:56,755
Or do you want me to give you a ride?

669
00:46:02,140 --> 00:46:04,902
Then I’ll go to class quickly

670
00:46:05,040 --> 00:46:06,564
And come back to treat your wound

671
00:46:07,173 --> 00:46:08,555
You’re still going to class?

672
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:15,413
You can stay alone, right?

673
00:46:16,528 --> 00:46:19,146
Yeah, no problem

674
00:46:22,150 --> 00:46:23,306
Then…

675
00:46:24,022 --> 00:46:26,502
Play a game and wait for me. I’ll be back soon

676
00:46:28,008 --> 00:46:29,973
I thought you’d skip class

677
00:46:34,040 --> 00:46:36,862
Why? Do you want me to stay?

678
00:46:38,693 --> 00:46:41,004
No need. Go to class

679
00:46:42,373 --> 00:46:43,300
Yeah

680
00:46:45,368 --> 00:46:47,617
Because you like diligent students.

681
00:46:50,297 --> 00:46:51,786
Call me if anything happens.

682
00:46:54,693 --> 00:46:55,422
I got it.

683
00:47:25,786 --> 00:47:26,844
Dan.

684
00:47:27,804 --> 00:47:30,297
Is there someone who remembers every detail about us?

685
00:47:31,128 --> 00:47:33,168
Why? What did Tiger remember?

686
00:47:36,170 --> 00:47:38,680
He used to skip class to see me often

687
00:47:38,924 --> 00:47:41,417
So I told him I like diligent students.

688
00:47:41,702 --> 00:47:44,764
I just said it casually so he’d stop skipping.

689
00:47:45,168 --> 00:47:46,355
But he actually did it.

690
00:47:48,813 --> 00:47:52,497
Haha, you like him more now, right?

691
00:48:03,124 --> 00:48:04,622
I like him even more.

692
00:48:04,875 --> 00:48:06,177
Idiot.

693
00:48:35,831 --> 00:48:37,240
Nue, are you free?

694
00:48:37,666 --> 00:48:39,493
Can I call you?

695
00:48:42,422 --> 00:48:43,560
What is it, Tiger?

696
00:48:43,924 --> 00:48:46,742
- What's wrong?
- Let’s get straight to it

697
00:48:47,213 --> 00:48:49,991
You know I’m courting Nao, right?

698
00:48:51,640 --> 00:48:54,391
But why I didn't feel anything go forward

699
00:48:54,982 --> 00:48:56,773
Why you feels the same?

700
00:48:57,408 --> 00:48:58,580
It’s the same as before

701
00:49:03,315 --> 00:49:05,182
Don’t put too much sauce yet, kid

702
00:49:05,777 --> 00:49:08,302
Yes, Auntie Maew, the sauce…

703
00:49:09,791 --> 00:49:10,822
Is this one?

704
00:49:12,013 --> 00:49:15,448
Tiger, taste it slowly first

705
00:49:15,831 --> 00:49:18,226
If it’s too bland, we can add more later, okay

706
00:49:18,920 --> 00:49:19,777
Yes, ma’am

707
00:49:30,013 --> 00:49:32,026
Mmm, it tastes good now

708
00:49:33,128 --> 00:49:34,520
Alright then

709
00:49:35,142 --> 00:49:36,746
I’ll go plate the food, Auntie Maew

710
00:49:37,008 --> 00:49:40,831
- Thank you so much - You’re welcome. If you want to make any other dish

711
00:49:41,000 --> 00:49:42,808
you can call me anytime, dear

712
00:49:43,422 --> 00:49:44,453
Yes, ma’am

713
00:50:10,568 --> 00:50:12,213
You’re awake?

714
00:50:12,675 --> 00:50:14,782
Come on, let’s eat. We’ll be late for class

715
00:50:24,755 --> 00:50:25,911
You made this yourself?

716
00:50:27,364 --> 00:50:28,351
Yeah

717
00:50:29,760 --> 00:50:32,275
I even called your mom to get the recipe.

718
00:50:32,560 --> 00:50:34,620
You really called my mom for the recipe?

719
00:50:37,168 --> 00:50:38,817
Come on, eat.

720
00:50:41,902 --> 00:50:43,360
Bon appétit.

721
00:51:08,488 --> 00:51:09,577
Ah, got it.

722
00:51:12,973 --> 00:51:14,942
I’ll come pick you up this evening

723
00:51:15,244 --> 00:51:16,822
Mm, go on then

724
00:51:40,853 --> 00:51:45,040
Study hard, okay — from Suer

725
00:51:51,591 --> 00:51:53,760
I do this for Nao every day

726
00:51:54,422 --> 00:51:56,640
But nothing seems to change

727
00:51:59,266 --> 00:52:02,577
Then what do you think dating is supposed to be like?

728
00:52:05,031 --> 00:52:07,662
There should be more to it, I guess

729
00:52:08,306 --> 00:52:10,031
Like when someone confesses love

730
00:52:10,520 --> 00:52:11,937
He just stays indifferent

731
00:52:12,537 --> 00:52:14,040
And even cursed me back

732
00:52:14,773 --> 00:52:15,902
Cursed you?

733
00:52:16,222 --> 00:52:17,417
“You idiot”

734
00:52:19,004 --> 00:52:22,342
Let me tell you something. When Nao called you an idiot…

735
00:52:22,460 --> 00:52:23,813
that means he was flustered

736
00:52:25,680 --> 00:52:26,871
Huh?

737
00:52:28,244 --> 00:52:31,800
Hey, Nue, sorry, I got startled

738
00:52:32,368 --> 00:52:34,715
- Nue, are you serious? - Yeah

739
00:52:35,155 --> 00:52:38,457
But that’s all I’ll say, I don’t want to spoil it yet

740
00:52:54,768 --> 00:52:55,964
Go take a shower

741
00:52:59,880 --> 00:53:00,720
Hey

742
00:53:03,786 --> 00:53:04,702
Nao

743
00:53:22,297 --> 00:53:23,280
Sit up a bit

744
00:53:24,271 --> 00:53:25,142
Careful

745
00:53:37,013 --> 00:53:37,937
Pork congee

746
00:53:56,160 --> 00:53:57,542
You really won’t go to the hospital?

747
00:54:05,440 --> 00:54:07,017
But I want to stay and take care of you

748
00:54:08,537 --> 00:54:11,164
Go on, I’ll sleep a bit more

749
00:54:14,275 --> 00:54:15,617
Okay

750
00:54:16,140 --> 00:54:17,684
But if anything happens

751
00:54:18,040 --> 00:54:19,426
Just call you

752
00:54:19,924 --> 00:54:20,880
I know

753
00:54:21,657 --> 00:54:22,693
Go on

754
00:54:23,097 --> 00:54:24,426
You’ll be late for class

755
00:54:26,453 --> 00:54:27,631
Okay

756
00:54:28,573 --> 00:54:31,253
Don’t move around too much, I’ll hurry back

757
00:54:37,453 --> 00:54:38,586
Eat too

758
00:54:53,564 --> 00:54:54,746
Go in, go in

759
00:54:55,182 --> 00:54:56,226
Got it

760
00:54:59,182 --> 00:55:00,488
Game over

761
00:55:00,786 --> 00:55:03,008
Not bad

762
00:55:03,140 --> 00:55:05,373
Nice, go in, beautiful

763
00:55:05,782 --> 00:55:07,697
- Nice
- North

764
00:55:09,280 --> 00:55:10,080
Oh

765
00:55:10,728 --> 00:55:12,711
Hey, you’re awake?

766
00:55:12,980 --> 00:55:14,075
Yeah

767
00:55:15,031 --> 00:55:15,915
Want some water?

768
00:55:17,368 --> 00:55:18,315
Here

769
00:55:41,760 --> 00:55:42,866
Did Suer send you here?

770
00:55:43,266 --> 00:55:44,088
Yeah

771
00:55:44,600 --> 00:55:46,608
I was free anyway, so I came

772
00:55:46,880 --> 00:55:49,182
Aren’t you bored? Coming to watch over me like this

773
00:55:49,355 --> 00:55:52,035
Hey, how could I be bored

774
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:54,853
I’m getting paid a thousand per hour

775
00:56:03,648 --> 00:56:04,675
Hey, North

776
00:56:06,093 --> 00:56:07,493
I’ve got something to tell you

777
00:56:08,244 --> 00:56:08,911
Mm

778
00:56:09,964 --> 00:56:11,342
I think…

779
00:56:12,568 --> 00:56:14,404
- I’m going to ask Suer to be my boyfriend
- Huh?

780
00:56:31,782 --> 00:56:33,853
Looking back at everything now

781
00:56:34,017 --> 00:56:36,502
everything he did for me was actually so good

782
00:56:36,804 --> 00:56:41,217
I do feel my heart race for my friend, but I don’t want him around me all the time

783
00:56:41,391 --> 00:56:43,977
So does that mean you’ve started liking him?

784
00:56:44,155 --> 00:56:45,968
Suer, let’s be together

785
00:56:48,911 --> 00:56:49,595
Suer.

786
00:56:49,790 --> 00:56:51,960
- Don’t die, okay - Is he badly hurt?

787
00:56:51,960 --> 00:56:52,915
I don’t know

788
00:56:52,915 --> 00:56:54,773
We were just talking and he suddenly passed out

789
00:56:55,097 --> 00:56:56,733
You said to me to bring a boyfriend…

790
00:56:57,271 --> 00:56:58,640
So I really brought one.
